INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("34","1","2025-03-15 14:30:21","2025-03-15 14:30:21","<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As the financial year 2024-2025 (FY25) draws to a close, it\'s essential for mutual fund investors to understand the prevailing&nbsp;<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/wealth/tax\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">tax</a>&nbsp;implications on their investments. Recent changes have altered the taxation landscape for both equity and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/topic/debt-mutual-funds\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">debt mutual funds</a>. Here\'s a comprehensive overview:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Taxation of Equity Mutual Funds</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Definition: Equity mutual funds are schemes that allocate at least 65{1760279bfa68b2eeb23183533ab546c652305f39cce91c9e71f5cd6ee092fdfc} of their assets to equity shares of domestic companies.</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:post-featured-image /-->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Short-Term Capital Gains (<a href=\"https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/topic/stcg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">STCG</a>)</strong>: If units are redeemed within 12 months of investment, the gains are classified as short-term. As per Section 111A of the Income-tax Act, 1961, STCG on such funds is taxed at 15{1760279bfa68b2eeb23183533ab546c652305f39cce91c9e71f5cd6ee092fdfc} for transfers made before July 23, 2024. For transfers on or after this date, the rate increases to 20{1760279bfa68b2eeb23183533ab546c652305f39cce91c9e71f5cd6ee092fdfc}.<br><br>Also Read | <a href=\"https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/mf/analysis/mutual-funds-increase-cash-allocation-by-rs-55000-crore-in-one-year-to-rs-1-87-lakh-crore/articleshow/118975100.cms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">MFs increase cash allocation by Rs 55,000 crore in one year to Rs 1.87 lakh crore</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Long-Term Capital Gains (LTCG):</strong> For units held beyond 12 months, the gains are considered long-term. According to Section 112A, LTCG exceeding Rs 1,25,000 is taxed at 10{1760279bfa68b2eeb23183533ab546c652305f39cce91c9e71f5cd6ee092fdfc} for transfers before July 23, 2024, and at 12.5{1760279bfa68b2eeb23183533ab546c652305f39cce91c9e71f5cd6ee092fdfc} for transfers on or after this date, provided the transfer is subject to Securities Transaction Tax (STT).</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->","Explained: How your mutual fund investments will be taxed in financial year 2025","","publish","open","open","","explained-how-your-mutual-fund-investments-will-be-taxed-in-financial-year-2025","","","2025-03-15 14:30:21","2025-03-15 14:30:21","","0","http://localhost/TheRegionalExpress/?p=34","0","post","","0");
